%20Mitch%20McConnell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChao's%20sudden%20death%20occurred%20in%20Blanco%20County%2C%20outside%20Austin%2C%20in%20the%20early%20morning%20hours%20of%20February%2011.%20Local%20police%20initially%20declined%20to%20share%20many%20details%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20still%20investigating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Blanco%20County%20sheriff%20released%2062%20pages%20of%20records.%20The%20documents%20said%20Chao's%20death%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bunfortunate%20accident.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20said%20that%20her%20blood-alcohol%20concentration%20was%200.233%20grams%20per%20100%20milliliters%2C%20which%20is%20about%20three%20times%20the%20legal%20limit%20of%200.08%20grams%20per%20100%20milliliters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20report%20said%20Chao%20was%20hosting%20a%20group%20of%20women%20at%20her%20ranch%20when%20she%20died.%20The%20group%20had%20dinner%20at%20the%20guest%20lodge%20on%20the%20property%20on%20Saturday%2C%20February%2010.%20Afterward%2C%20at%20around%2011%3A30%20p.m.%20Chao%20planned%20to%20drive%20from%20one%20building%20on%20the%20ranch%20to%20another%20because%20it%20was%20cold%20outside.%20But%20after%20getting%20into%20her%20car%2C%20she%20accidentally%20reversed%20into%20a%20pond%2C%20police%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20describes%20how%20Chao's%20friends%2C%20an%20employee%2C%20and%20first%20responders%20attempted%20to%20save%20her%20from%20the%20pond%2C%20which%20was%20situated%20between%20the%20main%20house%20and%20the%20guest%20house%20on%20the%20remote%20ranch.%20Even%20though%20one%20of%20the%20back%20doors%20of%20the%20car%20was%20open%2C%20officers%20could%20not%20pull%20her%20out%20of%20it%2C%20and%20it%20took%20them%20several%20minutes%20to%20break%20the%20driver's%20side%20window%20and%20extract%20her%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20said%20Chao%20and%20the%20Tesla%20had%20been%20in%20the%20water%20for%20around%2021%20minutes%20by%20the%20time%20they%20arrived%20on%20the%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile