igure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERegina%20Smith%2C%2034%2C%20owned%20three%20homes%20and%20wanted%20to%20buy%20another%20to%20rent%20out.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESmith%20inadvertently%20sent%20her%20%2460%2C000%20down%20payment%20to%20a%20scammer.%20Then%20her%20home%20purchase%20fell%20through.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReal-estate%20scams%20and%20wire%20fraud%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20and%20can%20affect%20even%20experienced%20buyers%20and%20sellers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERegina%20Smith%20had%20found%20a%20two-bedroom%20house%20in%20the%20historic%20district%20of%20Memphis%2C%20Tennessee.%20It%20was%20over%20100%20years%20old%20with%20lots%20of%20character%20in%20an%20artsy%20part%20of%20town%20%E2%80%94%20perfect%20for%20a%20short-term%20rental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20offer%20of%20%24280%2C000%20was%20accepted%20and%20she%20prepared%20for%20closing%20in%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Smith%20had%20bought%20three%20houses%20previously%2C%20she'd%20used%20a%20cashier's%20check%20to%20deliver%20the%20down%20payment%20or%20brought%20the%20money%20to%20the%20title%20company's%20office.%20Because%20loans%20for%20investment%20properties%20often%20require%20a%20bigger%20down%20payment%2C%20she%20was%20dealing%20with%20a%20larger%20sum%20of%20money%3A%20%2460%2C000.%20She%20anticipated%20having%20to%20wire%20the%20money%20before%20closing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20before%20the%20scheduled%20closing%2C%20Smith%20received%20an%20email%20that%20appeared%20to%20be%20from%20the%20title%20company%20and%20included%20instructions%20about%20where%20to%20wire%20the%20%2460%2C000.%20She%20obliged%2C%20sending%20the%20funds%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20an%20hour%20later%2C%20she%20received%20an%20email%20with%20wire%20instructions%20from%20the%20real%20title%20company.%20The%20first%20email%20was%20fake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20thing%20I%20felt%20was%20complete%20and%20utter%20despair%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20could%20not%20believe%20this%20was%20happening%20to%20me.%20I%20sat%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20I%20cried%20for%20maybe%2045%20minutes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20was%20a%20victim%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwire-fraud%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewire%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20broad%20term%20that%20refers%20to%20a%20group%20of%20criminal%20activities%20that%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fphishing-scams-in-your-inbox-waiting-to-steal-your-money-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemail%20phishing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20money%20laundering.%20The%20FBI's%20Internet%20Crime%20Complaint%20Center%20received%20over%20880%2C000%20complaints%20about%20internet%20scams%20totaling%20%2412.5%20billion%20in%20losses%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20a%2049%25%20increase%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20lost%20the%20previous%20year.%20Real-estate%20wire%20fraud%20falls%20under%20the%20category%20of%20business%20email%20compromise%2C%20or%20BEC%2C%20according%20to%20the%20FBI.%20In%20the%20FBI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ic3.gov%2FHome%2FAnnualReports%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternet%20Crime%20Complaint%20Center's%20annual%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20BEC%20was%20the%20second-costliest%20crime%2C%20behind%20investment%20fraud%2C%20in%202022%2C%20with%20a%20reported%20%242.9%20billion%20in%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20more%20people%20are%20falling%20victim%20to%20real-estate%20crimes.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20FBI%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fland-fraud-home-title-theft-prevention-tips-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%2C578%20people%20lost%20%24350%2C328%2C166%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20real-estate%20scams%2C%20a%2064%25%20increase%20from%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20showing%20how%20common%20it's%20become.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.certifid.com%2Fstate-of-wire-fraud%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20report%20from%20the%20wire-fraud-protection%20company%20CertifID%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20one%20in%2020%20homebuyers%20and%20sellers%20were%20victims%20of%20real-estate%20fraud%20in%20the%20past%20three%20years%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20median%20loss%20exceeding%20%2470%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20is%20not%20alone.%20A%20retired%20couple%20in%20New%20Jersey%2C%20who%20got%20conned%20by%20a%20real-estate%20wire-fraud%20scam%20in%202017%20when%20they%20were%20looking%20to%20buy%20a%20smaller%20house%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fmoney%2Fscams-fraud%2Finfo-2023%2Freal-estate-wire-fraud.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20AARP%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20wired%20%2491%2C500%20to%20the%20wrong%20person%20after%20they%20got%20an%20email%20from%20someone%20impersonating%20their%20real-estate%20attorney.%20Similarly%2C%20Virginia%20resident%20Darryl%20Aldrich%20sent%20%2428%2C000%20to%20a%20fraudster%20when%20buying%20a%20house%2C%20even%20showing%20up%20to%20his%20closing%20with%20the%20email%20as%20proof%20of%20payment%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20title%20officer%20couldn't%20accept%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20our%20hearts%20just%20sank%20at%20that%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20Aldrich%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Flifestyle%2Freal-estate-fraud-risk-on-rise-victims-sounding-alarm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThat%20money%20was%20just%20gone%20out%20of%20our%20account.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20to%20Smith%2C%20who%20was%20hardly%20a%20wide-eyed%20newcomer%20to%20the%20real-estate%20market%2C%20shows%20that%20these%20scams%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20Smith%20was%20deceived%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Smith's%20case%2C%20the%20fraudster%20was%20able%20to%20hack%20into%20the%20title%20company's%20system%20and%20access%20the%20details%20of%20the%20sale%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20date%20of%20the%20closing%20and%20the%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20impersonate%20the%20title%20company%20in%20their%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20made%20it%20look%20as%20if%20this%20information%20came%20directly%20from%20the%20title%20company%20that%20we%20were%20utilizing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20it%20looked%20almost%20identical%20to%20previous%20email%20correspondence%20that%20we%20received.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Highways%20converge%20in%20downtown%20Memphis%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20as%20they%20approach%20the%20Mississippi%20River.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d0997b788914e55534fae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHighways%20converge%20in%20downtown%20Memphis%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20as%20they%20approach%20the%20Mississippi%20River.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Coletti%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it%20wasn't%20Smith's%20first%20time%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20she%20admitted%20she%20got%20caught%20up%20in%20the%20familiar%20excitement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHindsight%20is%20always%202020%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20excited%20about%20this%20deal%20that's%20about%20to%20happen%2C%20you've%20been%20working%20towards%20it%2C%20you%20finally%20see%20the%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20almost%20like%20you%20have%20rose-colored%20glasses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20reread%20the%20scammers'%20email%20later%2C%20Smith%20noticed%20some%20red%20flags%2C%20like%20an%20extra%20character%20in%20the%20name%20of%20her%20realtor%2C%20who%20was%20cc'd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it's%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20she%20was%20misled%3A%20The%20hackers%20had%20enough%20information%20to%20imitate%20someone%20who'd%20been%20involved%20in%20the%20home-sale%20transaction%20from%20the%20beginning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20had%20the%20exact%20closing%20costs%20down%20to%20the%20cent%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20had%20the%20address%20of%20the%20home%2C%20a%20closing%20date%2C%20time%2C%20and%20location.%20They%20had%20the%20assistant's%20name%20that%20worked%20for%20the%20title%20company%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20as%20if%20they'd%20previously%20received%20emails%20or%20correspondence%20from%20this%20individual%20because%20they%20were%20able%20to%20mirror%20that%20person's%20signature%2C%20their%20title%2C%20their%20entire%20profile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESmith%20got%20her%20money%20back%20but%20lost%20the%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20realizing%20she%20made%20a%20mistake%2C%20Smith%20reached%20out%20to%20her%20title%20company%2C%20the%20bank%2C%20local%20law%20enforcement%2C%20and%20the%20FBI%2C%20who%20put%20her%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20Secret%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20wired%20the%20funds%20on%20a%20Thursday%2C%20and%20by%20Monday%2C%20the%20%2460%2C000%20was%20back%20in%20her%20bank%20account%20thanks%20to%20the%20help%20of%20her%20local%20Secret%20Service%20branch%2C%20Smith%20said.%20(The%20Secret%20Service%20had%20not%20yet%20responded%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20before%20publication.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomebuyers%20are%20able%20to%20recover%20funds%2028%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20CertifID%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20was%20happy%20to%20get%20her%20money%20back%2C%20but%20it%20cost%20her%20that%20house.%20Without%20the%20down%20payment%2C%20Smith%20was%20unable%20to%20close%20on%20the%20house%2C%20and%20the%20sellers%20chose%20a%20different%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20she's%20happy%20with%20the%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20able%20to%20find%20another%20property%2C%20and%20actually%2C%20it%20all%20worked%20out%20for%20the%20good%20because%20the%20property%20that%20we%20found%20is%2010%20times%20better%2C%26quot%3