%20Naxalism%20should%20be%20there.%20Rights%20are%20not%20given%3B%20they%20have%20to%20be%20snatched%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20veteran%20Dalit%20leader%20told%20Nair%20off-the-record%20when%20asked%20for%20a%20comment%20on%20the%20recent%20arrest%20of%20an%20academic-activist%20in%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20case.%20He%20cringed%20at%20the%20label%20%E2%80%9Curban-naxal%E2%80%9D%20that%20was%20being%20widely%20used%20to%20justify%20the%20arrest%2C%20Nair%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20New%20Delhi%20launch%20of%20her%20first%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERam%20Vilas%20Paswan%2C%20The%20Weathervane%20of%20Indian%20Politics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Roli%20Books%2C%20Nair%20said%20that%20Paswan%E2%80%99s%20remark%20on%20Naxalism%2C%20that%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20pen%20down%20as%20a%20journalistic%20copy%2C%20sowed%20the%20idea%20in%20her%20head%20to%20write%20his%20biography%20someday%20%E2%80%93%20something%20that%20she%20also%20conveyed%20to%20the%20leader%20who%20is%20now%20no%20longer%20alive%20to%20read%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20book%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20is%20not%20an%20insider%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20as%20many%20may%20know%20Paswan%20much%20better%20than%20I%20did.%20I%20wrote%20it%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20an%20inquisitive%20curiosity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nair%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20was%20launched%20by%20the%20deputy%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Harivansh%20Narayan%20Singh.%20The%20launch%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20panel%20discussion%20on%20the%20future%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBahujan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epolitics%20in%20India%20by%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20MP%20Manoj%20Kumar%20Jha%2C%20former%20diplomat%20and%20politician%20Pavan%20K.%20Varma%20and%20senior%20journalist%20Rasheed%20Kidwai.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEveryone%20at%20the%20event%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2019)%20agreed%20that%20Paswan%E2%80%99s%20remark%20on%20Naxalism%20reflected%20Paswan%E2%80%99s%20deep%20understanding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20caste-ridden%20society%20and%20his%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20empower%20the%20marginalised%20despite%20his%20several%20flip-flops%20that%20earned%20him%20the%20title%20of%20%3Cem%3Emausam%20vaigyanik%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20weathervane%20of%20Indian%20politics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-contradictions-between-ram-vilas-paswans-personal-beliefs-and-professional-compulsions%5C%22%3EThe%20Contradictions%20between%20Ram%20Vilas%20Paswan%E2%80%99s%20Personal%20Beliefs%20and%20Professional%20Compulsions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarivansh%20praised%20the%20book%20for%20its%20deep%20research%20and%20readability%20while%20disagreeing%20with%20the%20title%20of%20the%20book.%20He%20said%20that%20reducing%20Paswan%20as%20the%20mausam%20vaigyanik%20buries%20his%20long%20history%20of%20struggles%20because%20of%20which%20he%20could%20emerge%20as%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20Dalit%20leaders%20of%20India.%20He%20recalled%20how%20Paswan%20walked%20miles%20to%20Darbhanga%20from%20his%20village%20to%20attend%20school%2C%20secured%20a%20position%20as%20a%20Deputy%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20(DSP)%20in%20state%20police%20before%20switching%20towards%20politics%20under%20the%20influence%20of%20tall%20socialist%20leaders%20like%20Jayprakash%20Narayan%20and%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20Paswan%20was%20consistent%20in%20advocating%20for%2015%25%20reservation%20for%20the%20poor%20across%20all%20castes%20throughout%20his%20political%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20was%20clear%20about%20his%20goals.%20As%20a%20Dalit%2C%20he%20understood%20the%20importance%20of%20being%20in%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20Harivansh%20said%2C%20while%20remembering%20his%20famous%20Lok%20Sabha%20speech%20on%20the%20infamous%201977%20caste%20massacre%20in%20Belchhi%2C%20Bihar%2C%20which%20forced%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20visit%20the%20village.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPaswan%2C%20a%20nine-term%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20and%20two-term%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20also%20had%20a%20distinguished%20record%20of%20winning%20the%201977%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20with%20the%20highest%20margin%20of%20nearly%204.5%20lakh%20votes.%20However%2C%20he%20also%20earned%20disrepute%20for%20switching%20political%20camps%20frequently%20to%20remain%20in%20ministerial%20positions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20he%20was%20a%20shrewd%20strategist.%20Given%20the%20background%20he%20came%20from%2C%20he%20was%20consistently%20concerned%20about%20the%20poor%2C%E2%80%9D%20Varma%20said%2C%20but%20added%20that%20while%20he%20saw%20his%20%E2%80%9Castuteness%E2%80%9D%20as%20his%20success%2C%20he%20also%20believed%20that%20one%20of%20his%20biggest%20failures%20was%20to%20let%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%20slip%20into%20a%20state%20of%20disarray.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20said%20that%20Paswan%20witnessed%20the%20breakdown%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBahujan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epolitics.%20However%2C%20even%20Varma%20disagreed%20with%20the%20title%20of%20the%20book.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20sub-head%20of%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98T%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20Weathervane%20of%20Indian%20Politics%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20refer%20to%20Ram%20Vilas%20Paswan%20is%20wrong.%20The%20title%20should%20go%20to%20someone%20else%20in%20Bihar%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20Varma%20said%2C%20taking%20a%20dig%20at%20his%20former%20party%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%E2%80%99s%20leader%20Nitish%20Kumar%20who%20appears%20to%20have%20outdone%20Paswan%20in%20switching%20political%20camps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPaswan%20was%20a%20sincere%2C%20genuine%20man%20who%20believed%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBahujan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epolitics.%20But%20he%20could%20not%20carry%20forward%20the%20legacy%20of%20his%20own%20politics%2C%E2%80%9D%20Varma%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJha%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20said%20that%20the%20decline%20of%20independent%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EBahujan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epolitics%20is%20also%20a%20result%20of%20Dalit%20MPs%20and%20MLAs%20being%20caged%20with%20their%20respective%20party%20whips%20in%20the%20parliament%20and%20assemblies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20increasing%20use%20of%20money%20in%20Indian%20elections%20and%20politics%20have%20prevented%20independent%20Dalit%20voices%20from%20reaching%20the%20mainstream.%20%E2%80%9CCapital%E2%80%99s%20grip%20is%20increasing%20in%20our%20politics.%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20imagine%20a%20voice%20like%20Paswan%20who%2C%20in%20his%20first%20electoral%20campaign%2C%20went%20around%20villages%20in%20a%20cycle%20to%20canvass%20for%20himself%20and%20reach%20out%20to%20people%2C%20can%20win%20an%20election%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710933655000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20153020%2FScreenshot-2024-03-20-at-3.29.52-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhow-ram-vilas-paswans-ideas-on-naxalism-inspired-journalist-sobhana-k-nair-to-pen-his-biography%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CThe%20book%20is%20not%20an%20insider%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20as%20many%20may%20know%20Paswan%20much%20better%20than%20I%20did.%20I%20wrote%20it%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20an%20inquisitive%20curiosity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nair%20said%20at%20the%20release%20of%20the%20book.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhow-ram-vilas-paswans-ideas-o