2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20135859%2Fcoal-mining-1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%2010%20villages%20in%20the%20coal-dependent%20districts%20of%20Jharkhand%20and%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20global%20language%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimatepromise.undp.org%2Fnews-and-stories%2Fwhat-just-transition-and-why-it-important%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20transitions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0falters.%20The%20idea%20of%20using%20economic%20diversification%2C%20alternative%20jobs%2C%20retraining%2C%20and%20reskilling%20loses%20its%20shine.%20In%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20the%20conversation%20revolves%20around%20creating%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjoint-research-centre.ec.europa.eu%2Fjrc-news-and-updates%2Fenergy-transition-can-provide-alternative-jobs-risk-coal-regions-2020-01-29_enhttps%3A%2Fjoint-research-centre.ec.europa.eu%2Fjrc-news-and-updates%2Fenergy-transition-can-provide-alternative-jobs-risk-coal-regions-2020-01-29_en%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubstitute%20livelihood%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20those%20affected%20by%20the%20phasing%20out%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20However%2C%20in%20Hazaribagh%2C%20Korba%2C%20Raigarh%2C%20and%20Ramgarh%2C%20locals%20are%20preoccupied%20with%20land%3A%20its%20loss%20to%20mining%2C%20their%20fight%20to%20retain%20it%2C%20and%20their%20dream%20to%20regain%20it.%20Those%20living%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20coal-mining%20sector%20say%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20trust%20jobs%20as%20only%20a%20few%20of%20them%20are%20formally%20or%20consistently%20engaged%20with%20the%20coal%20economy.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20keeps%20them%20focused%20on%20issues%20of%20land%20ownership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahuatand%2C%20a%20Santhal%20village%20in%20Ramgarh%20district%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20is%20an%20example%20of%20what%20the%20closure%20of%20coal%20mining%20can%20set%20off%20in%20rural%20communities%20around%20mines.%20With%20the%20first%20energy%20transition%E2%80%94when%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funacademy.com%2Fcontent%2Fupsc%2Fstudy-material%2Fpublic-administration%2Fpublic-sector-undertakings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublic%20sector%20undertaking%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(PSU)%20set%20up%20its%20mine%20in%20the%201980s%E2%80%94residents%20lost%20their%20agricultural%20land%20and%2C%20hence%2C%20their%20generational%20wealth%20and%20food%20security.%20They%20became%20almost%20entirely%20dependent%20on%20the%20coal%20job%20economy.%20The%20jobs%20are%20few.%20While%20the%20handful%20of%20employees%20still%20continue%20to%20receive%20their%20salary%2C%20this%20source%20may%20soon%20run%20its%20course%20as%20the%20mine%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Franchi%2F8-coal-mines-shut-in-ramgarh-for-over-a-year-production-loss-pegged-at-12l-metric-tonnes-daily%2Farticleshow%2F86948950.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBablu%20Hembrom%2C%20who%20fought%20for%20a%20job%20with%20the%20mining%20company%20and%20finally%20secured%20it%20in%202016%2C%20goes%20in%20daily%20to%20mark%20his%20attendance.%20Father%20of%20two%2C%20Bablu%20knows%20the%20future%20is%20uncertain%20for%20the%20younger%20residents%20of%20the%20remote%20village.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20us%20regret%20the%20decision%20our%20parents%20or%20grandparents%20took%20in%201964%20to%20swap%20agricultural%20land%20for%20compensation%20or%20jobs.%20Coal%20mining%20started%20in%201984.%20The%20money%20we%20received%20as%20compensation%20has%20run%20out%20for%20many%20of%20us.%20Jobs%20came%20to%20only%20one%20person%20in%20each%20family.%20That%20will%20also%20not%20last.%20In%20the%20future%2C%20we%20will%20end%20up%20as%20beggars%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20According%20to%20Sarpanch%20Kiran%20Devi%2C%20approximately%2075%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20here%20is%20unemployed.%20%E2%80%9CWorking-age%20adults%2C%20even%20when%20they%20have%20education%20and%20degrees%2C%20are%20financially%20dependent%20on%20their%20parents.%E2%80%9D%20Biju%20Oraon%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20other%20industries%20develop%2C%20will%20there%20be%20enough%20jobs%20for%20all%20of%20us%3F%E2%80%9D%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20help%20that%2C%20so%20far%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20renewable%20energy%20is%20concentrated%20in%20some%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Frenewables-integration-in-india%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esouthern%20and%20western%20states%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Shivpal%20Bhagat%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Oraon%20community%20and%20is%20the%20sarpanch%20of%20Kosampali%20village%2C%20Raigarh%2C%20tells%20us%20that%20his%20family%20has%20lived%20in%20the%20area%20for%20four%20generations%20but%20they%20have%20never%20known%20such%20financial%20insecurity%20before.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20floundering%20since%20we%20gave%20up%20our%20land%20in%202007.%20We%20were%20expecting%20development%20and%20thought%20we%20would%20get%20stable%20employment.%20Instead%2C%20only%20a%20few%20of%20us%20get%20jobs%2C%20that%20too%20of%20lower%20grades%2C%20and%20with%20contractors.%E2%80%9D%20His%20brother%20Kuldeep%20Bhagat%20pitches%20in%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20our%20parents%20sold%20the%20land%2C%20they%20were%20not%20equipped%20with%20the%20necessary%20information%20or%20understanding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fcoal-mining-1-1.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELand%20should%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20indigenous%20people%20or%20the%20farmers%20who%20originally%20owned%20it.%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20International%20Accountability%20Project%20%2F%20CC%20BY%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20conflicted%20relationship%20with%20coal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20mining%20activity%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergy.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fcoal%2Ffebruary-2024-sees-11-83-jump-in-indias-coal-production-cil-leads-with-8-69-growth%2F108234485%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasing%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20India%20opened%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fnews%2Fcentre-issues-allocation-orders-to-successful-bidders-of-22-coal-blocks-123060800965_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E22%20new%20coal%20mines%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0between%202015%20and%202022%2C%20and%20has%20another%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eco-business.com%2Fnews%2Findias-growing-informal-coal-workforce-complicates-energy-transition%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBetween%25202015%2520and%25202022%252C%2520India%2Cworld%252C%252078%2520are%2520in%2520India.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E93%20proposed%20coal%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20the%20other%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1016936%2Fin-indias-coal-belts-jobs-are-now-hard-to-get-and-harder-to-keep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemployment%20in%20the%20coal%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20not%20seen%20growth.%20The%20use%20of%20mechanisation%2C%20private%20contractors%2C%20and%20mine%20development%20operators%20(MDOs)%20has%20resulted%20in%20fewer%20and%20more%20informal%20engagements.%20By%20some%20estimates%2C%20the%20number%20of%20contractual%20and%20informal%20workers%20in%20the%20sector%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fchrome-extension%2F%2Fefaidnbmnnnibpcajpcglclefindmkaj%2Fhttps%3A%2Fiforest.global%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F05%2FInformal-workers-in-coal-regions-in-India_final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2.4%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20of%20formal%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20residents%20allege%20that%20contractors%20and%20MDOs%20prefer%20people%20from%20other%20states%2C%20often%20their%20own%2C%20for%20most%20of%20the%20work.%20Migrants%20are%20put%20up%20in%20camps%20inside%20the%20mines%20and%20work%20daily%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20they%20add.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20believe%20we%20take%20too%20many%20leave%20days%20and%20prefer%20the%20migrants%20who%20are%20available%20at%20all%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20alleges%20a%20local%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20locals%20working%20in%20the%20coal%20sector%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20conflicted%20relationship%20with%20it.%20Two%20men%20from%20Churchu%20in%20Hazaribagh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20say%20they%20are%20grateful%20for%20the%20jobs%20they%20secured%20as%20compensation%20for%20their%20ancestral%20land.%20However%2C%20requesting%20anonymity%2C%20both%20allege%20they%20get%20their%20payslips%20from%20different%20companies%20every%20couple%20of%20months.%20They%20are%20confused%20about%20who%20they%20are%20employed%20with%20and%20wonder%20what%20the%20terms%20will%20be%20if%20they%20are%20laid%20off%20and%20whether%20they%20will%20be%20compensated.%20In%20Sarasmal%20village%2C%20a%20guard%20now%20hired%20by%20a%20contractor%20reports%20that%20he%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20his%20cleaning%20job%20with%20the%20mining%20company%20as%20one%20of%20his%20eyes%20was%20deemed%20weak%20after%20a%20medical%20examination.%20In%20Tapranga%2C%20Raigarh%2C%20union%20leaders%20for%20local%20employees%20tell%20us%20they%20would%20be%20devastated%20to%20lose%20their%20jobs%20but%20complain%20about%20how%20houses%20crack%20or%20break%20because%20the%20mine%20is%20too%20close%20to%20their%20colony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bhujangkachar%2C%20located%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20a%20mine%20in%20Korba%20district%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Bhagwan%20Das*%20who%20lost%20his%20agricultural%20land%20to%20mining%2C%20is%20worried%20that%20the%20excavation%20is%20now%20moving%20closer%20to%20his%20house.%20His%20son%20Shyam%20Das%2C*%20who%20lives%20with%20him%2C%20has%20a%20contractual%20job%20with%20the%20very%20company%20about%20to%20take%20over%20the%20land%20where%20his%20house%20stands.%20Many%20of%20his%20peers%20live%20with%20this%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fno-other-work-villagers-cling-to-coal-despite-damaged-farms-and-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eambiguity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Ransahi%20Sonpakat%2C%20says%20he%20prefers%20to%20hedge%20his%20bets%20for%20the%20future.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20like%20to%20continue%20farming%20the%20land%20I%20have%20remaining%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20not%20as%20much%20as%20before.%20My%20children%20may%20get%20a%20job.%20If%20not%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20have%20land%20so%20they%20can%20use%20it%20for%20agriculture%20later%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20with%20cracks%20in%20its%20walls_coal%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FA-house-with-cracks-from-mining-blasts_resized.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHouses%20crack%20or%20break%20because%20the%20mine%20is%20too%20close%20to%20the%20colony.%20%7C%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20Debojit%20Dutta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20land%2C%20no%20food%20security%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%2042%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20in%20Jharkhand%20and%20about%2029%20percent%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niti.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2021-11%2FNational_MPI_India-11242021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultidimensionally%20poor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20locals%20equate%20land%20ownership%20with%20food%20security.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20always%20had%20food%20when%20we%20had%20our%20own%20land.%20Now%20we%20need%20to%20pay%20for%20everything.%20The%20salary%20is%20not%20adequate%20for%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ram%20Sewak%20Badal%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20rehabilitation%20colony%20in%20Dhenga%2C%20Jharkhand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Sarasmal%2C%20Bhagwati%20Bhagat%2C%2060%2C%20says%20she%20used%20to%20run%20her%20house%20on%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emahua%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Etendu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20other%20forest%20pickings.%20%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20for%20six%20months%20and%20that%20was%20enough%20to%20feed%20my%20family%20for%20the%20whole%20year.%20There%20is%20such%20little%20forest%20produce%20now.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20to%20get%20to%20the%20forest%2C%20I%20walk%20across%20the%20mine.%20It%20is%20steep%20and%20dangerous.%20We%20used%20to%20eat%20so%20much%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emoringa%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(drumstick)%20earlier.%20Now%20it%20is%20covered%20in%20soot%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20wash%20it%20many%20times%20before%20we%20can%20cook%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Local%20women%20who%20worked%20as%20agricultural%20labour%20or%20made%20a%20livelihood%20from%20forest%20produce%20are%20deeply%20affected%20by%20coal-related%20displacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mahuatand%2C%20many%20migrate%20to%20other%20regions%20and%20states%20for%20sustenance.%20Others%2C%20however%2C%20succumb%20to%20the%20informal%20coal-gathering%20economy.%20A%20queue%20of%20women%20and%20adolescents%20climb%20down%20a%20precarious%20dirt%20path%20into%20the%20valley%2C%20mobiles%20in%20their%20hand%20so%20they%20can%20use%20them%20as%20torches.%20People%20with%20a%20smaller%20build%20fare%20better%20in%20the%20dark%20underground%20mine.%20The%20company%20has%20made%20a%20trench%20around%20the%20abandoned%20mine%20to%20prevent%20them%20from%20going%20in.%20But%20the%20coal%20gatherers%20have%20broken%20a%20passage%20through%20it.%20Ram%20Manjhi*%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20collect%20and%20sell%20this%20coal%2C%20we%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20cook%20dinner.%20If%20the%20coal%20is%20carried%20out%20in%20trucks%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20development.%20But%20if%20we%20carry%20it%20out%20on%20our%20bicycles%20and%20motorcycles%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20stealing.%E2%80%9D%20One%20of%20the%20many%20people%20displaced%20by%20mining%2C%20Manjhi%20received%20neither%20compensation%20nor%20a%20job.%20After%20he%20vacated%20his%20house%2C%20he%20moved%20closer%20to%20the%20forest.%20He%20alleges%20forest%20officials%20filed%20a%20case%20against%20him%20for%20encroachment%20on%20forest%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bicycle%20carrying%20coal_coal%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FA-bicycle-carrying-coal_resized.jpg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22680%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELocals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%20%7C%20Picture%20courtesy%3A%20Debojit%20Dutta%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%20is%20critical%20for%20survival%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERural%20communities%20currently%20facing%20land%20acquisition%20by%20newer%20mining%20projects%20have%20learned%20from%20the%20history%20of%20%E2%80%98coal%E2%80%99%20villages.%20In%20villages%20such%20as%20Jugra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20and%20Pelma%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20locals%20persistently%20protest%20displacement.%20Chunnulal%20Soren%2C%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ektaparishadindia.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEkta%20Parishad%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0activist%20from%20Vishnugarh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20says%20locals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESudhlal%20Saw%20is%20a%20sugarcane%20farmer%20in%20Jugra%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20and%20his%20family%20of%20two%20sons%2C%20daughters-in-law%2C%20and%20grandchildren%20work%20together%20to%20produce%20jaggery.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20refuse%20to%20convert%20my%20generational%20wealth%20to%20money.%20It%20will%20turn%20us%20from%20masters%20of%20our%20land%20to%20servants%20elsewhere.%20Look%20at%20what%20is%20happening%20all%20around.%20Will%20they%20give%20jobs%20to%20all%20of%20us%20for%20every%20generation%3F%E2%80%9D%20Kailash%20Saw%2C%20an%20activist%20in%20the%20village%2C%20points%20out%20the%20folly%20in%20using%20fertile%20land%20for%20excavations.%20%E2%80%9CBarkagaon%20(the%20village%20he%20lives%20in)%20is%20part%20of%20what%20is%20known%20as%20the%20rice%20bowl%20of%20the%20region.%20Why%20are%20we%20using%20this%20land%20for%20mining%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamdular%20Saw%2C%20a%20schoolteacher%20in%20Jugra%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20are%20they%20acquiring%20land%20now%20if%20they%20have%20to%20close%20down%20the%20mine%20in%20three%20or%20four%20decades%3F%20History%20has%20taught%20us%20not%20to%20give%20up%20our%20land%20for%20short-term%20gains.%E2%80%9D%20In%202018%2C%20the%20residents%20of%20Jugra%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2FNTPC-land-acquisition-houses-villagers-demolished-jharkhand-jugra%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomplained%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20district%20administration%20that%20land%20was%20being%20acquired%20forcefully%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20locals%20have%20been%20protesting%20industrial%20mining%20with%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Frights%2Fcoal-satyagraha-adivasis-reclaim-their-natural-resources%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoal%20satyagraha%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0since%202011.%20In%20Pelma%2C%20Chhatisgarh%2C%20there%20is%20a%20near%20consensus%20that%20mining%20won%E2%80%99t%20change%20their%20fortunes%20for%20the%20better%20but%20for%20the%20worse.%20Rajbala*%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Pelma%2C%20believes%20it%20will%20be%20disastrous%20to%20give%20up%20her%20land.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20be%20a%20big%20loss.%20I%20want%20my%20children%20to%20stay%20here%20and%20continue%20with%20agriculture.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShivpal%20Bhagat%20speaks%20for%20most%20people%20affected%20by%20mining%20in%20the%20region%20when%20he%20says%20that%20jobs%20in%20future%20industries%20will%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20secure%20their%20sustenance.%20%E2%80%9CAgricultural%20land%20is%20critical%20to%20our%20survival%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20Shivpal%20was%20among%20the%20petitioners%20who%20sought%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frights%2Fnational-green-tribunal-jindal-power-coal-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20damages%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20a%20mining%20company%20for%20failing%20to%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20remedy%20the%20topsoil%20they%20had%20destroyed.%20He%20says%20that%20mining%20companies%20should%20follow%20the%20law%20and%20level%20the%20land%20when%20they%20are%20done%2C%20restoring%20the%20topsoil%20so%20it%20can%20be%20reused%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20local%20communities.%20Union%20leaders%20at%20Tapranga%20say%20that%20even%20infertile%20land%20will%20help%20as%20locals%20can%20use%20it%20for%20fishery%2C%20animal%20husbandry%2C%20and%20other%20livelihood%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F10%2Findia-needs-legal-framework-for-closing-mines-and-power-plants%2Fhttps%3A%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2022%2F10%2Findia-needs-legal-framework-for-closing-mines-and-power-plants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elacks%20the%20legal%20framework%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0necessary%20to%20facilitate%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Fclimate-emergency%2Fcan-india-undo-its-unjust-transition-from-coal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etransfer%20of%20land%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0back%20to%20the%20communities.%20Ramesh%20Sharma%2C%20national%20coordinator%20at%20Ekta%20Parishad%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20government%20has%20taken%20the%20land%20for%20mining%2C%20it%20can%20transfer%20this%20land%20to%20another%20project%20or%20lease%20it%20to%20a%20private%20company.%20Even%20if%20renewable%20energy%20grows%2C%20private%20companies%20will%20get%20large%20tracts%20of%20land%20to%20run%20solar%20or%20wind%20farms.%20But%20land%20should%20be%20returned%20to%20the%20indigenous%20people%20or%20the%20farmers%20who%20originally%20owned%20it.%20It%20can%20be%20co-owned%20by%20communities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%20120%20districts%20in%20the%20country%20have%20sizeable%20fossil-fuel%20or%20related%20industries%20and%20they%20have%20one-fourth%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20population.%20For%20a%20just%20transition%2C%20India%20may%20need%20to%20consider%20a%20strategy%20appropriate%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20affected%20locals%2C%20and%20these%20needs%20are%20rooted%20in%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*%3Cem%3ENames%20changed%20to%20maintain%20confidentiality%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2Farticle%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fidronline.org%2F%5C%22%3EIndia%20Development%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710924351000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20135859%2Fcoal-mining-1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rural%20communities%20currently%20facing%20land%20acquisition%20by%20newer%20mining%20projects%20have%20learned%20from%20the%20history%20of%20%E2%80%98coal%E2%80%99%20villages.%20Locals%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20coal%20industry%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sustained%20for%20long%20and%20that%20they%20may%20lose%20their%20land%20for%20nothing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-coal-communities-are-more-worried-about-land-than-jobs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Goon%20Squad'%20officers%20jailed%20for%20'despicable'%20torture%20of%20two%20black%20men%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710922800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F70x70%2Fskynews-hunter-elward-jeffrey-middleton_6495538.jpg%3F20240320073720%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmississippi-goon-squad-officers-jailed-for-torturing-two-black-men-13098433%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20former%20Mississippi%20sheriff's%20deputies%20who%20were%20members%20of%20a%20group%20calling%20itself%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Goon%20Squad%26quot%3B%20have%20been%20handed%20lengthy%20prison%20sentences%20for%20their%20part%20in%20torturing%20two%20black%20men.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fmississippi-goon-squad-officers-jailed-for-torturing-two-black-men-13098433%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmississippi-goon-squad-officers-jailed-for-torturing-two-black-men-13098433%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fmississippi-goon-squad-officers-jailed-for-torturing-two-black-men-13098433%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BJP%20Govt%20Printed%20EBs%20Worth%20Rs%208%2C350%20Cr%20After%20SC%20Reserved%20Verdict%20on%20Scheme%3A%20RTI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20133735%2FScreenshot-2024-03-20-at-1.37.24-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20printed%208%2C350%20electoral%20bonds%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20each%20in%202024%20alone%2C%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20already%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20scheme%20in%20November%202023.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20information%20was%20revealed%20in%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20(SBI%E2%80%99s)%20response%20to%20transparency%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20query.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%208%2C350%20crores%20printed%20this%20year%20are%20more%20than%20what%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20amassed%20through%20the%20scheme%20since%20its%20inception.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%20published%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhow-much-money-did-the-bjp-really-get-from-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3EBJP%20has%20received%20Rs%208%2C251.8%20crores%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20since%202018.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20total%20value%20of%20bonds%20sold%20in%20this%20period%20is%20Rs%2016%2C518%20crore.%20This%20means%20the%20BJP%20redeemed%20about%2050%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F17197297%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20earlier%20RTI%20filed%20by%20Batra%20had%20established%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Felectoral-bonds-tax-payers-cost-printing-bank-commission%5C%22%3Etaxpayer%2C%20not%20the%20donors%20or%20political%20parties%2C%20is%20footing%20the%20bill%20of%20printing%20and%20managing%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESBI%2C%20the%20bank%20authorised%20to%20issue%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20had%20charged%20Rs%2013.50%20crore%20to%20the%20government%20towards%20its%20%E2%80%9Ccommission%2C%20printing%20and%20other%20expenses%20for%20managing%20and%20operating%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Scheme%2C%E2%80%9D%20between%202018-2023%2C%20the%20RTI%20response%20had%20revealed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20cost%20of%20printing%20and%20managing%20the%20additional%208%2C350%20bonds%20this%20year%20is%20not%20yet%20known.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20appears%20that%20the%20government%20was%20confident%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo.%20That%20was%20why%20it%20went%20ahead%20with%20printing%20more%20bonds%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%2C%E2%80%9D%20Batra%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20February%2015%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20calling%20it%20unconstitutional%20and%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20this%20information%2C%20the%20court%20had%20directed%20the%20SBI%20to%20furnish%20the%20details%20of%20the%20bonds%20to%20the%20EC.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710922334000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20133735%2FScreenshot-2024-03-20-at-1.37.24-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbjp-govt-printed-ebs-worth-rs-8350-cr-after-sc-reserved-verdict-on-scheme-rti%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%208%2C350%20crore%20printed%20this%20year%20are%20more%20than%20Rs%208251.8%2C%20or%20what%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20has%20amassed%20through%20the%20scheme%20since%20its%20inception.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A159%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbjp-govt-printed-ebs-worth-rs-8350-cr-after-sc-reserved-verdict-on-scheme-rti%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Modi%20Has%20Failed%20Where%20Nehru%20Had%20Succeeded%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20115055%2FUntitled-design-14.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20elections%20approach%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20strides%20across%20the%20political%20arena%20as%20if%20unchallenged.%20No%20other%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20exuded%20such%20brimming%20confidence%20in%20their%20public%20appearances%2C%20though%20some%20may%20believe%20that%20Indira%20Gandhi%20came%20quite%20close.%20Nehru%2C%20despite%20the%20adulation%20of%20his%20compatriots%2C%20mostly%20appeared%20weighed%20down%20by%20the%20responsibilities%20he%20had%20assumed%20and%20the%20restraint%20he%20had%20imposed%20upon%20his%20deportment.%20The%20understatedness%2C%20however%2C%20concealed%C2%A0%20a%20gameplan.%20This%20was%20to%20quicken%20India%E2%80%99s%20moribund%20economy%2C%20an%20aspect%20missed%20by%20most%20of%20his%20biographers%20who%20have%20invariably%20devoted%20much%20of%20their%20attention%20to%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20ambitions%20and%20internal%20political%20preoccupations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActually%2C%20in%20their%20focus%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20share%20a%20common%20factor.%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20speech%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20August%2014%20had%20declared%20that%20the%20goal%20of%20independence%20was%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbuild%20up%E2%80%9D%20a%20%E2%80%9Cprosperous%E2%80%9D%20country.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20did%20express%20caution%20in%20assuming%20that%20this%20was%20assured.%20Modi%2C%20ever%20confident%20of%20his%20capabilities%2C%20has%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20emphatic.%20He%20launched%20his%20election%20campaign%20of%202014%20with%20the%20unambiguous%20promise%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAchche%20din%20aanewale%20hai%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E.%20For%20the%20majority%20in%20India%2C%20better%20days%20can%20only%20mean%20economic%20betterment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20effect%2C%20both%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20emphasised%20the%20importance%20of%20economic%20growth%2C%20and%20staked%20their%20political%20career%20on%20the%20progress%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%E2%80%99s%20position%20is%20revealed%20in%20the%20following%20statement%20he%20made%20in%20parliament%20in%20May%201956%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20whole%20philosophy%20is%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20every%20possible%20way%20of%20growth%20and%20not%20to%20do%20something%20which%20suits%20some%20doctrinaire%20theory%20or%20imagine%20we%20have%20grown%20because%20we%20have%20satisfied%20some%20text-book%20maxim%20of%20a%20hundred%20years%20ago.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%2C%20who%20prefers%20his%20delivery%20upfront%2C%20considered%20the%20maxim%20%E2%80%9Cminimum%20government%2C%20maximum%20governance%E2%80%9D%20sufficient.%20It%20is%20interesting%20to%20spot%20a%20character%20similarity%20between%20these%20two%20otherwise%20ideologically%20opposed%20politicians.%20Firstly%2C%20they%20did%20not%20shy%20way%20from%20declaring%20publicly%20what%20they%20intended%20to%20deliver%2C%20and%20gave%20the%20people%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20they%20would%20achieve%20it.%20This%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20behaviour%20of%20most%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20politicians%20today.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20know%20what%20they%20stand%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20do%20the%20records%20of%20these%20two%20powerful%20prime%20ministers%20of%20India%20stack%20up%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%3F%20The%20recent%20announcement%20by%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Office%20of%20an%20advance%20estimate%20of%20GDP%20in%202023-24%20gives%20us%20data%20for%20the%20full%20decade%20for%20which%20Modi%20has%20been%20prime%20minister.%20This%20yields%20a%20definite%20picture.%20Far%20from%20having%20accelerated%20after%202014%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%20has%20slowed%20since%202016.%20This%20need%20not%C2%A0%20surprise.%202016%20was%20the%20year%20of%20the%20demonetisation.%20Though%20only%C2%A0%20a%20temporary%20shock%2C%20as%20the%20money%C2%A0%20supply%20returned%20to%20its%20earlier%20level%20quite%20quickly%2C%20the%20shortage%20of%20currency%20could%20have%20triggered%20forces%20making%20for%20slower%20growth%20which%20feed-off%20of%20one%20another.%20The%20economy%20slowed%20for%20three%20successive%20years%2C%20and%20in%202020-21%20it%20actually%20contracted.%20Not%20even%20the%20high%20growth%20rates%20post%20Covid%20have%20been%20sufficient%20to%20negate%20the%20impact%20of%20four%20years%20of%20progressively%20slowing%20growth.%20Everything%20points%20to%20the%20role%20of%20demonetisation%20in%20this%20as%20none%20of%20the%20exogenous%20drivers%20of%20growth%2C%20namely%20world%20demand%2C%20agricultural%C2%A0%20growth%20or%20public%20investment%20slowed%20at%20the%20time.%20Whatever%20may%20be%20the%20reason%2C%20we%20now%20know%20that%20the%20economic%20policies%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%20have%20not%20delivered%20faster%20growth%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%20in%20what%20may%20be%20termed%20the%20Nehru%20era%2C%20lasting%20till%20his%20death%20in%201964%2C%20is%20stark.%20With%20the%20implementation%20of%20policies%20to%20revive%20the%20economy%2C%20gathered%20under%20the%20rubric%20%E2%80%98planning%E2%80%99%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20rate%20accelerated%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20fifties%20and%20remained%20steady%20till%201964.%20In%20the%20annals%20of%20twentieth%20century%20growth%20the%20Nehru%20era%20was%20pathbreaking.%20While%20we%20have%20reliable%20data%20only%20for%20the%20last%20fifty%20years%20of%20the%20Raj%2C%20we%20know%20that%20the%20colonial%20era%20was%20a%20time%20of%20stagnant%2C%20if%20not%20declining%2C%20per%20capita%20income.%20This%20trend%20was%20decisively%20reversed%20in%20the%20fifties.%20Per%20capita%20income%20has%20not%20stagnated%20since%20then%2C%20though%20growth%20faltered%20for%20about%20a%20decade%20and%C2%A0%20a%20half%20after%20the%20passing%20of%20Nehru.%20The%20transition%20in%20the%20fifties%20to%20a%20permanently%20higher%20growth%20path%20may%20be%20regarded%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98mother-of-all%E2%80%99%20economic%20transitions%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20recorded%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20accounts%20for%20this%20differential%20record%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%3F%20Above%20all%2C%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20Indian%20economic%20policy%20was%20guided%20by%20a%20definite%20strategy.%20This%20was%20to%20to%20try%20and%20energise%20an%20economy%20trapped%20at%20a%20low%20level%20of%20income%20via%20a%20big%20push%20to%20be%20provided%20through%20rising%20public%20investment.%20The%20reliance%20on%20public%20investment%20was%20entirely%20for%20practical%20reasons.%20It%20was%20believed%20that%20the%20private%20sector%20was%20unlikely%20to%20come%20up%20with%20the%20level%20of%20investment%20required%20to%20shock%20the%20economy%20into%20motion%20due%20to%20the%20long%20gestation%20period%20and%20high%20uncertainty%20involved.%20This%20strategy%20paid-off%20handsomely.%20As%20the%20Indian%20state%20invested%2C%20so%20did%20the%20private%20sector.%20Most%20would%20be%20surprised%20to%20know%20that%20during%20the%20Nehru%20era%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20private%20sector%E2%80%99s%20investment%20exceeded%20that%20of%20the%20public%20sector%3Cstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20context%2C%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0t%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehis%20should%20not%20surprise%20anyone%2C%20for%2C%20as%20public%20investment%20increases%20it%20generates%20demand%2C%20thus%20expanding%20the%20market%20to%20be%20had%20by%20the%20private%20sector.%20It%20is%20this%20mechanism%20that%20explains%20the%20ending%20of%20what%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20period%20of%20about%20two%20centuries%20of%20stagnation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20succeeded%20where%20Modi%20failed%20because%20he%20had%20a%20strategy%20for%20growth.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20advisors%20seemed%20to%20have%20encouraged%20him%20to%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20slogans%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cminimum%20government%E2%80%9D%2C%20for%20instance.%20The%20trouble%20is%20that%20the%20pursuit%20of%20minimum%20government%20can%20result%20in%20less%20of%20both%20public%20and%20private%20investment%2C%20as%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20the%20mechanism%20by%20which%20growth%20was%20achieved%20in%20the%201950s%20in%20India.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20private%20investment%20rate%20in%20India%20has%20barely%20budged%20since%202014%2C%20despite%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20avowedly%20business-friendly%20government.%20Having%20finally%20sensed%20the%20folly%20of%20being%20ideologically%20committed%20against%20a%20public%20presence%20in%20the%20economy.%20his%20government%20has%20used%20the%20last%20two%20budgets%20to%20unleash%20a%20blitzkrieg%20of%20infrastructure%20building%20before%20the%20ending%20of%20its%20term%20this%20coming%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20is%20to%20even%20remotely%20suggest%20that%20the%20policies%20of%20the%20Nehru%20era%20were%20ideal.%20First%2C%20exports%20were%20ignored%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20there%20was%20no%20way%20of%20funding%20even%20the%20intermediate%20inputs%20and%20capital%20goods%20needed%20for%20the%20industrialisation%20drive%2C%20leave%20alone%20the%20defence%20equipment%20and%20crude%20oil.%20This%20showed%20up%20in%20the%20balance%20of%20payments%20crises%20that%20had%20plagued%20India%20in%20the%20fifties%20and%20sixties.%20Secondly%2C%20there%20was%20the%20momentous%20neglect%20of%20primary%20education%2C%20especially%20for%20women%2C%20which%C2%A0%20slowed%20the%20adoption%20of%20technology%20and%20better%20practices%20more%20generally%2C%20in%20every%20sphere%20of%20life.%20Human%20development%20would%20not%20only%20have%20led%20to%20a%20much%20faster%20eradication%20of%20poverty%20in%20India%2C%20it%20was%20the%20very%20promise%20of%20Indian%20independence.%20Perhaps%20the%20planners%20imagined%20that%20it%20would%20come%20along%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20growth.%20It%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20as%20if%20growth%20should%20be%20the%20sole%20economic%20indicator%20we%20ought%20to%20be%20concerned%20with%20but%20it%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20history%20that%20both%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20chose%20to%20locate%20it%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20their%20economic%20policy.%20This%20makes%20it%20a%20criterion%20by%C2%A0%20which%20we%20may%20evaluate%20the%20difference%20they%20made%20to%20the%20economy%20in%20their%20time%20as%20prime%20ministers%20of%20India.%20Nehru%20quickened%20the%20economy%20in%20his%20time.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20is%20yet%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPulapre%20Balakrishnan%20is%20an%20economist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710916245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20115055%2FUntitled-design-14.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-has-failed-where-nehru-had-succeeded%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20accounts%20for%20this%20differential%20record%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Modi%20with%20respect%20to%20economic%20growth%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-has-failed-where-nehru-had-succeeded%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Inequality%20at%20Historic%20High%3B%20Wealth%20Concentration%20Shot%20Up%20Sharpest%20Between%202014-5%20and%202022-3%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13093230%2Fkarthik-chandran-uwSbfD1afxI-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Paris-based%20World%20Inequality%20Lab%2C%20with%20pathbreaking%20work%20into%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwid.world%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWorldInequalityLab_WP2024_09_Income-and-Wealth-Inequality-in-India-1922-2023_Final.pdf%5C%22%3Ehas%20a%20paper%20out%20on%20the%20state%20of%20inequality%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Titled%2C%20%3Cem%3EIncome%20and%20Wealth%20Inequality%20in%20India%2C%201922-2023%3A%20The%20Rise%20of%20the%20Billionaire%20Raj%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20has%20found%20on%20analysing%20data%20between%201922%20and%202022%20(a%20century%20of%20data%20on%20incomes%20and%20wealth)%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CBy%202022-23%2C%20top%201%25%20income%20and%20wealth%20shares%20(22.6%25%20and%2040.1%25)%20are%20at%20their%20highest%20historical%20levels%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%201%25%20income%20share%20is%20among%20the%20very%20highest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20higher%20than%20even%20South%20Africa%2C%20Brazil%20and%20US.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20%E2%80%98billionaire%20raj%E2%80%99%20(a%20term%20used%20to%20define%20the%20post-2010s%20rapid%20rise%20of%20billionaires%20in%20the%20country%2C%20at%20odds%20with%20lives%20of%20millions%2C%20popularised%20by%20James%20Crabtree%E2%80%99s%20book%20of%20the%20same%20name)%20is%20now%20more%20unequal%20than%20the%20British%20colonial%20raj%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20two%20other%20observations%2C%20one%20on%20income%20tax%20being%20regressive%2C%20if%20seen%20from%20the%20prism%20of%20net%20wealth%20in%20society.%20Also%2C%20the%20poor%20economic%20data%2C%20which%20has%20%E2%80%9Cseen%20a%20decline%20recently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20finds%20that%20while%20inequality%20has%20been%20rising%20sharply%20in%20India%20since%20the%201980s%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbetween%202014-15%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%C2%A0rise%20of%20top-end%20inequality%20has%20been%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20terms%20of%20wealth%20concentration.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20listed%20five%20%E2%80%9CKey%20findings%E2%80%9D%20as%20follows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C1.%20Inequality%20declined%20post-independence%20till%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20after%20which%20it%20began%20rising%20and%20has%20skyrocketed%20since%20the%20early%202000s.%20Trends%20of%20top%20income%20and%20wealth%20shares%20track%20each%20other%20over%20the%20entire%20period%20of%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20Between%202014-15%20and%202022-23%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20top-end%20inequality%20has%20been%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20terms%20of%20wealth%20concentration.%20By%202022-23%2C%20top%201%25%20income%20and%20wealth%20shares%20(22.6%25%20and%2040.1%25)%20are%20at%20their%20highest%20historical%20levels%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%201%25%20income%20share%20is%20among%20the%20very%20highest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20higher%20than%20even%20South%20Africa%2C%20Brazil%20and%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20In%20line%20with%20earlier%20work%2C%20the%20paper%20finds%20suggestive%20evidence%20that%20the%20Indian%20income%20tax%20system%20might%20be%20regressive%20when%20viewed%20from%20the%20lens%20of%20net%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20A%20restructuring%20of%20the%20tax%20code%20to%20account%20for%20both%20income%20and%20wealth%2C%20and%20broad-based%20public%20investments%20in%20health%2C%20education%20and%20nutrition%20are%20needed%20to%20enable%20the%20average%20Indian%2C%20and%20not%20just%20the%20elites%2C%20to%20meaningfully%20benefit%20from%20the%20ongoing%20wave%20of%20globalization.%20Besides%20serving%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20fight%20inequality%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Csuper%20tax%E2%80%9D%20of%202%25%20on%20the%20net%20wealth%20of%20the%20167%20wealthiest%20families%20in%202022-23%20would%20yield%200.5%25%20of%20national%20income%20in%20revenues%20and%20create%20valuable%20fiscal%20space%20to%20facilitate%20such%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20paper%20emphasises%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20economic%20data%20in%20India%20is%20notably%20poor%20and%20has%20seen%20a%20decline%20recently.%20It%20is%20therefore%20likely%20that%20these%20new%20estimates%20represent%20a%20lower%20bound%20to%20actual%20inequality%20levels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20512px)%2085vw%2C%20512px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j.png%20512w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20112906%2FGJDFOJDbsAAYQ6j-300x231.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-702452%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20World%20Inequality%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20are%20Nitin%20Kumar%20Bharti%2C%20Lucas%20Chancel%2C%20Thomas%20Piketty%2C%20and%20Anmol%20Somanchi%20who%20have%20pulled%20together%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20income%20accounts%2C%20wealth%20aggregates%2C%20tax%20tabulations%2C%20rich%20lists%2C%20and%20surveys%20on%20income%2C%20consumption%2C%20and%20wealth%20in%20a%20consistent%20framework%20to%20present%20long%20run%20homogeneous%20series%20of%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government%20of%20India%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20has%20been%20adept%20at%20refuting%20any%20global%20assessments%20pointing%20to%20economic%20facts%20such%20as%20hunger%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20while%20not%20having%20made%20data%20available%20at%20regular%20intervals%20as%20was%20the%20case%20earlier.%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20data%20itself%20is%20highly%20contested.%20Former%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20Arvind%20Subramanian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fgdp-numbers-are-mystifying-dont-add-up-former-cea-arvind-subramanian%23%3A~%3Atext%3Deconomy-%2C%2527GDP%2520Numbers%2520Are%2520Mystifying%252C%2520Don%2527t%2520Add%2520Up%2527%2C5%2525%252C%2527%2520he%2520said.%5C%22%3Ehas%20expressed%20surprise%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20how%20the%20GDP%20has%20been%20said%20to%20be%20rising.%20India%20has%20missed%20its%20date%20for%20the%20decadal%20census%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20140%20years%2C%20in%202021%2C%20citing%20COVID-19.%20India%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-is-disputing-indias-covid-death-numbers-so-govt-wants-to-bury-global-report%5C%22%3Ehas%20issues%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20WHO%20data%20on%20underestimation%20of%20the%20Covid%20death%20toll%20by%20ten%20times.%20It%20is%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20which%20contests%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20Covid%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710915070000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F13093230%2Fkarthik-chandran-uwSbfD1afxI-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Findias-inequality-at-historic-high-wealth-concentration-shot-up-sharpest-between-2014-5-and-2022-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Data%20on%20India%20for%20a%20century%20has%20revealed%20income%20and%20wealth%20inequality%20now%20as%20being%20worse%20than%20during%20British%20colonial%20rule%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Inequality%20Lab.%20Using%20%E2%80%9Cbillionaire%20raj%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20present%20times%2C%20research%20has%20found%20that%20inequality%20declined%20post-independence%20till%20the%201980s%2C%20rose%20afterwards%20and%20is%20%E2%80%9Cskyrocketing%20now%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Findias-inequality-at-historic-high-wealth-concentration-shot-up-sharpest-between-2014-5-and-2022-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kerala%3A%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Lone%20Muslim%20Candidate%20%E2%80%98Sidelined%E2%80%99%20at%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Roadshow%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F20111215%2FGJBaWRLWQAAmam1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20or%20CPI(M)%20accused%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20of%20sidelining%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20(BJP)%20lone%20Muslim%20candidate%20in%20Kerala%20during%20a%20roadshow%20in%20the%20state%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2019).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20conducted%20a%20roadshow%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EPalakkad%20with%20candidates%20from%20Palakkad%20and%20the%20adjacent%20Ponnani%20constituency%20(Malappuram%20district).%20However%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Malappuram%20candidate%20Abdul%20Salam%20was%20not%20invited%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20event%2C%20PTI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Findia%2Frow-over-sidelining-bjps-lone-muslim-candidate-at-modis-roadshow-in-kerala-2943961%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECPI(M)%20leader%20A.K.%20Balan%20said%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAbdul%20was%20deliberately%20sidelined%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20roadshow%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Findia%2Frow-over-sidelining-bjps-lone-muslim-candidate-at-modis-roadshow-in-kerala-2943961%5C%22%3Ereflecting%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20attitude%20towards%20religious%20minorities.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fkerala%2Flok-sabha-elections-ldf-attacks-pm-modi-over-alleged-sidelining-of-lone-bjp-muslim-face-in-kerala-from-roadshow%2F%5C%22%3ESalam%20refuted%20the%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20that%20his%20constituency%20did%20not%20have%20any%20connection%20with%20Palakkad%20district%2C%20adding%20that%20that%20the%20Ponnani%20candidate%2C%20Niveditha%20Subramanian%2C%20was%20a%20part%20of%20the%20roadshow%20as%20the%20Ponnani%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20also%20includes%20the%20Thrithala%20assembly%20segment%20of%20Palakkad%20district.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20heard%20some%20candidates%20were%20going%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20roadshow.%20I%20was%20not%20invited%20to%20it.%20I%20did%20not%20go%20there%20to%20take%20part%20in%20the%20roadshow.%20I%20went%20there%20to%20meet%20Modi%20and%20invited%20him%20to%20Malappuram%2C%20Salam%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesouthfirst.com%2Fkerala%2Flok-sabha-elections-ldf-attacks-pm-modi-over-alleged-sidelining-of-lone-bjp-muslim-face-in-kerala-from-roadshow%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3ESouth%20First%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20%3